<F P=100> REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA </F>
<H3> <TI>   PAC's Alexander Calls Off Talk of Pact With ANC </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB0803132194 Johannesburg SAPA in English 1226 GMT 8 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> MB0803132194 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg SAPA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by C Molusi] </F>
  [Text] Johannesburg March 8 SAPA -- Negotiations on a 
proposed election pact between the African National Congress 
[ANC] and the Pan Africanist Congress [PAC] have collapsed, PAC 
Secretary General Benny Alexander said in Johannesburg on 
Tuesday [8 March]. Mr Alexandra said talks floundered after a 
media statement attributed to ANC President Nelson Mandela 
demanded a declaration of assets ahead of the election pact. 
"The PAC will contest the election on its own, in its own 
name," he said. Mr Alexander said the ANC was pursuing the 
election pact as a merger between two companies, which indicated 
a lack of commitment on the part of the organisation. 

</TEXT>

