<F P=100> REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Minister To Go Ahead With Housing Subsidy Scheme </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB0903122594 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network in 
English 1100 GMT 9 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB0903122594 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Housing Minister Louis Shill says he will go ahead 
with his 90,000 million rand housing subsidy scheme despite the 
Transitional Executive Council's [TEC] order for him not to do 
so. The TEC ordered Mr. Shill to stop the scheme yesterday, 
accusing the government of abusing its position for electoral 
gain. However, Mr. Shill said the sole objective of his 
department was to enable people to obtain adequate housing. Mr. 
Shill is not required to comply with the order as it has no 
force or effect on the government. 
  Mr. Shill said the principles and details of the scheme had 
been negotiated with a wide variety of organizations over a 
protracted period. The scheme has being implemented within the 
current budget, and no new money had been allocated. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

