<F P=101> Angola </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government Reports UNITA Captures Ship Near Soyo </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB0803170194 Johannesburg Channel Africa Radio in English 
1600 GMT 8 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB0803170194 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg Channel Africa Radio </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Angolan authorities say they have lost contact 
with a ship apprehended by UNITA [National Union for the Total 
Independence of Angola] forces in northern Angola, near the 
border with Zaire. Officials say the ship was transporting an 
unknown number of civilians, who had been prevented from 
disembarking. It is now docked at the (Cuanda) oil 
installations, near the city of Soyo, which is under UNITA's 
control. 

</TEXT>

