<F P=100> SOUTHERN AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Mozambique </F>
<H3> <TI>   Unomoz Updates Troop Confinement Figures </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB0803184394 Maputo Radio Mozambique Network in Portuguese 
1730 GMT 8 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB0803184394 </F>
<F P=104>  Maputo Radio Mozambique Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Portuguese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] More than 440 government soldiers turned up at 
assembly areas throughout the country yesterday. According to 
the UN Operations in Mozambique's [Unomoz] daily report, the 
Mozambique National Resistance [Renamo] confined slightly more 
than 700 men to their assembly areas yesterday. The two sides 
have already sent a total of more than 39,200 men to the 
confinement areas. 

</TEXT>

