<H3> <TI>   Nigerian Foreign Minister Arrives in Yaounde </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AB0903213494 Paris AFP in French 2039 GMT 9 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> AB0903213494 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> French </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Yaounde, 9 Mar (AFP) -- Nigerian Foreign Minister 
Alhaji Babagana Kingibe arrived today in Yaounde where he is 
likely to be received tomorrow by President Paul Biya concerning 
the border dispute between the two countries, it is learned from 
a source close to the Cameroonian Government. 
  Cameroonian Government sources have refused to make any 
comment on the purpose of the Nigerian foreign minister's visit 
which has not been officially announced. 
  Since the Bakassi Peninsula border dispute broke out between 
the two countries at the end of December 1993, both Cameroon and 
Nigeria have sent out several diplomatic missions to their 
neighbors in a bid to try to settle the dispute. In connection 
with such diplomatic missions, Kingibe first went to Yaounde in 
early January. 

</TEXT>

