<H3> <TI>   Italian Troops Complete Withdrawal From Mogadishu </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1003090394 Rome RAI Televideo Teletext in Italian 0706 GMT 
10 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1003090394 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome RAI Televideo Teletext </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Italian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The flag no longer flies on the roof of the former 
Italian embassy in Mogadishu. It was lowered at 0718 this 
morning. Five members of the "Colonel Moschin" battalion lowered 
the flag -- the same five men who had raised the tricolor on 15 
December 1992. 
  There are no more Italian troops in Mogadishu. Some 
divisions remain in Jowhar, where this morning General Carmine 
Fiore, the commander of the Italian contingent, will hand over 
the "Italia" hospital in the town to the non-governmental 
organization, InterSos. The hospital will be run by Italian and 
Somali doctors. 

</TEXT>

