<H3> <TI>   Police Deny RSA Involvement </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB0903174494 Johannesburg SAPA in English 1714 GMT 9 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> MB0903174494 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg SAPA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Mmabatho March 9 SAPA -- Bophuthatswana police have 
denied reports of South African Police involvement in a march by 
striking teachers on the South African Embassy in Mmabatho on 
Wednesday [9 March]. In a statement, Bophuthatswana police 
rejected the report which said South African Police were called 
in to assist when the teachers clashed with Bophuthatswana 
policemen. 
  "This is untrue. Although a Bophuthatswana police contingent 
was present, these men kept their distance as they had been 
requested to do," the statement said. 

