<H3> <TI>   Police Demand Reincorporation </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB1003141294 Johannesburg SAPA in English 1333 GMT 10 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> MB1003141294 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg SAPA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by L. Elias] </F>
  [Text] Mmabatho March 10 SAPA -- About 200 Bophuthatswana 
policemen on Thursday [10 March] afternoon assembled outside the 
South African Embassy in Mmabatho and handed over a memorandum 
demanding the homeland's re-incorporation into South Africa, 
full pay-out of their pension fund contributions and the 
opportunity to participate in free and fair elections. 
  "We no longer want to kill our brothers," they said while 
waiting to hand over the memorandum to Ambassador Dr Tjaart van 
der Walt. 

</TEXT>

