<F P=100> REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Mangope Rejects Reincorporation </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB1003065994 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network in 
English 0500 GMT 10 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB1003065994 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] Unrest in Bophuthatswana has claimed the life of 
a policeman. The policeman was on duty in Mabopane when he was 
shot by members of the public. In other incidents yesterday 13 
people were wounded in Mafikeng, and a policeman's house was 
burned down in Mmabatho. [passage omitted] 
  Meanwhile President Lucas Mangope of Bophuthatswana has said 
he is prepared to resist incorporation into South Africa even if 
he is left with only 50 soldiers. Addressing senior officers of 
the Bophuthatswana Defense Force in Mmabatho, Mr. Mangope said 
he had been promised military assistance from outside the state 
which he had turned down. 
  According to a senior officer who attended the meeting, 
members of the defense force defied the president by refusing to 
sing the national anthem. 

</TEXT>

