<F P=100> REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Strike, Violence Continues Stores 10 Mar </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB1003082394 Johannesburg SAPA in English 0800 GMT 10 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> MB1003082394 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg SAPA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By L. Elias] </F>
  [Text] Mmabatho March 10 SAPA -- A stayaway in 
Bophuthatswana on Thursday [10 March] turned Mafikeng and a 
giant shopping centre in Mmabatho into virtual ghost towns. 
Central Mafikeng was quiet with few people on the pavements and 
most stores closed. 
  Mmabatho's shopping complex Mega City had a few people 
strolling in the malls but all the shops were shut. Nearby 
government offices also appeared to be deserted with little sign 
of activity. 
  The Universiy of Bophuhatswana [Unibo], where students and 
police clashed on Wednesday, was also almost deserted with a few 
students continuing to man the gates that were barricaded on 
Wednesday. The barricades across the street at the entrance to 
Unibo had been removed, and only a garbage skip, a number of 
road signs and other debris remaining. 
  Youths had erected barricades at the entrance of Soweting 
township between Mafikeng and Mmabatho and were not allowing 
anyone into the area where, on Wednesday night, running battles 
between youths and police were reported on Wednesday night. A 
spotter plane circled the area on Thursday. 

</TEXT>

