<H3> <TI>   Freedom Front, IFP Fail To Submit Candidate Lists </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB0903164694 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network in 
English 1600 GMT 9 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB0903164694 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The newly founded Freedom Front of General Constand 
Viljoen and the Inkatha Freedom Party [IFP] of Dr. Mangosuthu 
Buthelezi are apparently not going to take part in the April 
election. Freedom Front representatives were present at the 
Independent Electoral Commission [IEC] in Johannesburg this 
afternoon, but did not submit the party's list of election 
candidates when they saw that the IFP was not there. 
  Earlier there was confusion over whether General Viljoen had 
submitted a candidates' list because he went into the IEC 
offices. A Conservative Party MP [Member of Parliament], Dr. 
Pieter Mulder, told the SABC [South African Broadcasting 
Corporation] that the Freedom Front did not hand a candidates' 
list to the IEC today. 
  Twenty-three of the 28 parties which registered for the 
election handed in candidates' lists this afternoon, with many 
of them arriving minutes before the deadline. The result was 
that the 4.30 deadline was extended to give the latecomers time 
to hand in their lists. 
  The ANC [African National Congress] and the PAC 
[Pan-Africanist Congress] were among the parties which arrived 
late. 

</TEXT>

