<H3> <TI>   Meyer Heckled During Speech </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB1003122894 Johannesburg SAPA in English 1152 GMT 10 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> MB1003122894 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg SAPA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by E. van Wyk] </F>
  [Text] Pretoria March 10 SAPA--Eggs were thrown at the 
stage from where Minister of Constitutional Development Roelf 
Meyer addressed an occasionally chaotic meeting at the 
University of Pretoria on Thursday [10 March]. 
  Mr Meyer's announcement that the government was prepared to 
negotiate with the Independent Electoral Commission and the 
Transitional Executive Council to allow further time for the 
Inkatha Freedom Party and the Freedom Front to submit their 
candidates lists was almost drowned out by right-wingers' chants 
and singing of the national anthem. 
  Mr Meyer said, however, the two parties should give a clear 
indication within the next 24 hours on whether they wanted to 
submit candidates lists. 
  Campus security personnel handcuffed and arrested a number 
of 
students after scuffles broke out in the hall. Right-wing 
students surged forward, yelling "Constand, Constand (Constand 
Viljoen, chairman of the Afrikaner Volksfront [National Front])" 
and heckled Mr Meyer. Mr Meyer said he would not be threatened, 
and that the university authorities should act against the 
errant students. 

</TEXT>

