<H3> <TI>   Three Killed on Way to March </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB0903172594 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network in 
English 1600 GMT 9 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB0903172594 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Three people were shot dead while on their way to an 
IFP [Inkatha Freedom Party] march at Port Shepstone on the Natal 
lower South Coast. Informed sources say the attack took place 
near Gamalakhe Township. 
  Earlier the IFP refused to allow members of the AWB 
[Afrikaner Resistance Movement] to join the march. The AWB 
members said they had gone to Port Shepstone to support Zulu 
King Zwelithini's demand for a sovereign kingdom and the Freedom 
Alliance's constitutional demands. Thousands of Zulus continued 
the march without the AWB members. 
  The group of protesters handed over a memorandum to the 
South 
African Police at Port Shepstone, supporting King Zwelithini's 
intercession in the negotiating process. Chief Khawula handed 
in the memorandum on behalf of the South Coast Zulu leaders. He 
said Zulus would never accept a flawed constitution. He said 
that not only did they reject the constitution, but they would 
actively resist it. 

</TEXT>

