<F P=101> Angola </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government Reportedly Moving Troops in Lunda </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB0903201794 Jamba Voz da Resistencia do Galo Negro in 
Portuguese 1900 GMT 9 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB0903201794 </F>
<F P=104>  Jamba Voz da Resistencia do Galo Negro </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Portuguese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Jose Eduardo dos Santos' army is moving large 
quantities of troops and war materiel in the diamond-rich area 
of Canfunfo in Lunda Norte Province. According to our 
correspondent in the area, the movement has been ordered by 
disillusioned Generals Sukissa and Luis Passeira. Preparations 
for a military offensive against diamond-producing UNITA areas 
have been going on for some time. The Armed Forces for the 
Liberation of Angola [FALA] has warned government troops not to 
accept such adventures because they will receive shameful and 
sad lessons since FALA will not tolerate any kind of aggression. 

</TEXT>

