<H3> <TI>   Soldiers Throw Grenades in Cabinda Market </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB0903143794 Johannesburg Channel Africa Radio in English 
1100 GMT 9 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB0903143794 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg Channel Africa Radio </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Sources say that at least 15 people were seriously 
injured in the oil rich Cabinda Enclave after two government 
soldiers threw hand grenades into a crowd of people in a market 
in the city of Cabinda, the provincial capital. The sources say 
that the two soldiers had been arrested after the incident. 
They say the soldiers had thrown the hand grenade into the 
crowd to create confusion to enable them to steal food from the 
local hawkers. 

