<H3> <TI>   National Reconciliation Talks Continue in Lusaka </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB0903200294 Jamba Voz da Resistencia do Galo Negro in 
Portuguese 1900 GMT 9 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB0903200294 </F>
<F P=104>  Jamba Voz da Resistencia do Galo Negro </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Portuguese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Progress is still being registered at the Lusaka 
peace talks. The National Union for the Total Independence of 
Angola [UNITA] and the government continue to discuss national 
reconciliation. A plenary meeting was held today and there is 
even talk of progress, but the information blackout imposed by 
mediator Alioune Blondin Beye continues to be respected. It is 
known, however, that the parties discussed aspects of specific 
principles of national reconciliation. 

</TEXT>

