<F P=101> Chad </F>
<H3> <TI>   Cabinet Adopts Budget for 1994 Fiscal Year </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AB1003143094 Ndjamena Radiodiffusion Nationale Tchadienne in 
French 1900 GMT 9 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> AB1003143094 </F>
<F P=104>  Ndjamena Radiodiffusion Nationale Tchadienne </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> French </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [All figures as heard] </F>
  [Text] President Idriss Deby this morning chaired an 
extraordinary cabinet meeting devoted to the examination of the 
draft bill on the 1994 budget. The general state budget for 
1994 was fixed at 203,329,800,000 CFA francs. Here is the 
report on the extraordinary cabinet meeting presented by the 
government spokesman, Communication Minister Ouardougou Bolou: 
  [Begin Bolou recording] The cabinet examined the only item 
on 
its agenda, namely the examination of the draft 1994 general 
budget bill. The general state budget for the 1994 fiscal year, 
which comprises recurrent expenditure for institutions and 
public investment expenditure and is worth 203,329,800,000 CFA 
francs, was adopted after extensive debate. This amount is 
broken down as follows: recurrent expenditure, 70,839,800,000 
francs; public investment budget, 132,783,000,000 francs. 
  The budget falls within an extremely difficult context for 
our country which is characterized by economic recession and the 
new financial situation brought about by the devaluation of the 
CFA franc. However, the government wants to rigorously take 
national imperatives into account, particularly the 
implementation of the transition guidelines and the honoring of 
its foreign commitments in line with measures to redress the 
serious macroeconomic imbalances of the country. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

