<H3> <TI>   Belgian Helicopter Crashes; 2 Injured </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  EA1003210094 Kigali Radiodiffusion Nationale de la 
Republique Rwandaise in French 1800 GMT 10 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA1003210094 </F>
<F P=104>  Kigali Radiodiffusion Nationale de la 
Republique Rwandaise </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> French </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A helicopter belonging to UNAMIR's Belgian 
contingent crashed into a high-voltage cable before crashing to 
the ground at about 1040 today in [words indistinct]. According 
to first reports from UNAMIR, the two persons aboard the 
helicopter suffered superficial cuts. 
  Meanwhile, Belgian Defense Minister Leo Delcroix was 
expected 
in Kigali early this evening. Indeed, Minister Delcroix has 
just landed with a delegation of over 10 parliamentarians and 
about 20 journalists. He will hold talks tomorrow morning with 
the UN secretary general's special representative to Rwanda, and 
at 1100 Mr. Booh-Booh will give a news conference at UNAMIR 
headquarters for the Belgian journalists and the national press. 

