<H3> <TI>   UNITA Reportedly Preparing Attack on Cuito </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB1103083194 Luanda TPA Television Network in Portuguese 
1930 GMT 10 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB1103083194 </F>
<F P=104>  Luanda TPA Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Portuguese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The political and military situation is once again 
shaky in the besieged city of Cuito. The National Union for the 
Total Independence of Angola's [UNITA] rebels continue to 
prepare a large-scale attack on the city of Cuito. The local 
press learned this from Captain Jorge Regresso, spokesman of the 
Angolan Armed Forces command, in the region. 
  According to the source, over the past few weeks, Savimbi's 
men have been carrying out constant movements of troops and war 
materiel from Andulo District and Huambo Province. They have 
also been planting mines, and kidnapping and assaulting 
civilians. 
  Jorge Regresso also said that more than 16 night flights, 
carrying large quantities of war materiel to Andulo, were 
registered from January to March. 

</TEXT>

