<F P=100> REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Violence Descends on Bophuthatswana as Government Flees </TI></H3>
<H4>   SADF Deployment Denied 10 Mar </H4>
<F P=102> MB1003194694 Johannesburg SAPA in English 1917 GMT 10 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> MB1003194694 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg SAPA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Johannesburg March 10 SAPA -- The South African 
Defence Force [SADF] has not been deployed in Bophuthatswana, 
South African Defence Ministry Communications Manager Dr DAS 
Herbst said in Johannesburg on Thursday night. 
  He said the SADF was not on a basis of alertness 
specifically 
with regard to Bophuthatswana. Dr Herbst was speaking against 
the background of ongoing speculation that the SADF had moved 
into the riotous homeland. 
  "Any decision about Bophuthatswana will be made by the South 
African Government and in which the Transitional Executive 
Council will be involved," Dr Herbst said. 
  He pointed out however that the SADF had, on an ongoing 
basis, contingency plans for all events. 

</TEXT>

