<H4>   ANC Denies MK Soldiers Present </H4>
<F P=102> MB1103083394 Johannesburg SABC TV 1 Network in English 0500 
GMT 11 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB1103083394 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg SABC TV 1 Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Afrikaner Volksfront [National Front] coleader, 
General Constand Viljoen, said he had information that members 
of the ANC's [African National Congress] military wing, Umkhonto 
we Sizwe [MK -- Spear of the Nation], were infiltrating into 
Bophuthatswana. He said it was high time for the Transitional 
Executive Council to intervene, and urged the ANC to stop its 
activities and to allow Bophuthatswana's cabinet to decide on 
reincorporation on Tuesday. 
  Meanwhile, ANC spokesman Carl Niehaus has denied in the 
strongest terms that MK soldiers were busy moving into 
Bophuthatswana. 

