<H3> <TI>   De Klerk Welcomes Mangope Decision on Election </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB1103142594 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network in 
English 1400 GMT 11 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB1103142594 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] President Lucas Mangope of Bophuthatswana is to 
recommend at an extraordinary meeting of Parliament in Mmabatho 
that the homeland participates in the election. [passage omitted] 
  State President F. W. de Klerk has welcomed the decision by 
President Mangope, saying this meant that Bophuthatswana could 
now give its full support to the electoral process. Addressing 
a news conference in Pretoria, President de Klerk said that the 
decision removed the main reason for the current unrest in 
Bophuthatswana. 

</TEXT>

