<H4>   Defense Force Recalled to Base </H4>
<F P=102> MB1003174594 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network in 
English 1600 GMT 10 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB1003174594 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] It is reported from Ciskei that all units of the 
homeland's defense force have been recalled to barracks, pending 
action the military plans to take to secure pensions under a new 
dispensation. It is believed that the military ruler of Ciskei, 
Brigadier Oupa Gqozo, is holding a cabinet meeting behind closed 
doors. All attempts to contact the Council of State have been 
unsuccessful. 
  Our East London news staff confirmed that military guards 
had 
been withdrawn from all government buildings and installations. 
The Ciskeian police have taken up positions around key points. 
Brig. Gqozo has been apparently in conference with his advisers 
throughout the day. The situation in the state is reported to 
be calm. 

</TEXT>

