<F P=102> MB1103073394 Johannesburg SAPA in English 0654 GMT 11 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> MB1103073394 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg SAPA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Johannesburg March 11 SAPA -- The situation in 
Ciskei is back to normal, with the military again in control of 
key government buildings and installations on Friday [11 March], 
reports SABC [South African Broadcasting Corporation] radio news. 
  On Thursday, the soldiers withdrew to their barracks 
demanding assurances from homeland leader Brig Oupa Gqozo about 
their future in a new dispensation. Brig Gqozo held talks with 
one Ciskei battalion on the outskirts of Bisho. 
  Ciskei minister of foreign affairs Mr Mickey webb said 
reports of an attempted coup were malicious rumours. He said 
Ciskeian soldiers had reaffirmed their support for Brig Gqozo at 
Thursday's meeting. 

