<H3> <TI>   Civil Servants `Not Planning an Uprising' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB1103135894 Johannesburg SAPA in English 1236 GMT 11 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> MB1103135894 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg SAPA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by E. Oelofse] </F>
  [Text] Bisho Mar 11 SAPA -- Ciskei's civil servants are not 
planning an uprising against the homeland government, SABC 
[South African Broadcasting Corporation] radio news reported. 
Ciskei Civil Servants Association (Cisa) Secretary General 
Mthimkhulu Mashiya said on Friday [11 March] that although there 
was dissatisfaction about pensions and related matters, civil 
servants had hoped their fears would be addressed by military 
ruler Brig Oupa Gqozo. 
  Mr Mashiya criticised Brig Gqozo, however, saying the Ciskei 
leader had found time to address his soldiers, but not the civil 
servants. 

