<H3> <TI>   Freedom Alliance Terminates `All Negotiations' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB1003171094 Johannesburg SAPA in English 1646 GMT 10 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> MB1003171094 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg SAPA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pretoria March 10 SAPA -- Freedom Alliance leaders 
have decided to terminate all negotiations and submission of 
candidates for the election, Afrikaner Volksfront [Afrikaner 
National Front] leader Constand Viljoen said on Thursday [10 
March]. 
  This stance would be maintained until the African National 
Congress stopped its action in Bophuthatswana, "so as to allow 
President Lucas Mangope to make the decisions to give up or 
maintain the sovereignity of the territory without being 
intimidated", Gen Viljoen said in a statement in Pretoria 
  Bophuthatswana is a Freedom Alliance member. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

