<F P=100> REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Two Killed, 26 Injured in Attack on Bus </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB1103090994 Johannesburg SAPA in English 0832 GMT 11 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> MB1103090994 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg SAPA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Johannesburg March 11 SAPA -- Two Amcoal Colliery 
workers were killed and 26 injured when gunmen opened fire on 
the bus taking them home to Thuthukani township near Standerton 
after the nightshift early on Friday [11 March] morning. 
  Standerton police said the motive for the attack was not yet 
known. An Anglo American Corporation statement on Friday said 
six of the injured were treated on site and 20 were taken to 
hospital. Two are seriously ill in Rand Mutual Hospital. 
  The statement said the morning shift had not gone 
underground 
and mine management was trying to restore calm. The names of 
the dead will be released when their next of kin have been 
notified. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

