<F P=100> WEST AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Benin </F>
<H3> <TI>   Military Exercise With France Enters Second Day </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AB1003143594 Dakar PANA in English 1050 GMT 10 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> AB1003143594 </F>
<F P=104>  Dakar PANA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Cotonou, 10 March (ABP-BEN/PANA) -- Troops from 
France and Benin mounted air and naval operations on Wednesday 
[9 March], the second day of the joint military exercise being 
organised by the two countries. 
  The BENIN PRESS AGENCY (ABP-BEN) said on Thursday that the 
operation, which took place in the high seas, about 20 km off 
the Cotonou port, was followed by the landing of troops on the 
beaches of the town. Three warships, two French--the "Rhin" and 
the "Grandiene"--and one from Benin, the "Patriote", as well as 
three French Mirage-F1 jet fighters, took part in the operation, 
the agency said. 
  The planes were moved from the French military base in 
Abidjan while the troops were brought in from garrisons in the 
Paris area. No incident was recorded during the operation, in 
which the French jets destroyed a "target" which was about to 
attack the warships. The landing of troops on the Cotonou 
beaches to push back an "enemy" attack ended the second day of 
the operations. 
  Observers from Niger, Togo, and Nigerian Armed Forces are 
observing the exercise which started Monday. It will end on 
Friday. 

</TEXT>

