<F P=100> EAST AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Uganda </F>
<H3> <TI>   Rebel Chief Killed in Shootout </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AB1103112194 Paris AFP in English 1017 GMT 11 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> AB1103112194 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Kampala, 11 March (AFP) -- Ugandan Government 
forces killed a rebel commander in a shootout that could signal 
the end of a residual insurgency in the north-east, Radio Uganda 
reported Friday [11 March]. The commander of the rebel Uganda 
People's Army (UPA), known simply as Abwongoto, was killed at a 
school in Kumi District on Wednesday where a handful of his 
fighters were reportedly trying to use children as human 
shields. His comrades, believed to number about a dozen, 
surrendered. 
  The UPA's fighters had dwindled to a few score in recent 
years, and it had degenerated into a bandit group, Western 
diplomats said. It was no longer considered a serious threat to 
the government of President Yoweri Museveni, which has largely 
succeeded in stamping out rebel activity. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

