<H3> <TI>   ULIMO's General Johnson `Reconciled' With Koromah </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AB1203132094 Paris AFP in French 1242 GMT 12 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> AB1203132094 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> French </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Monrovia, 12 Mar (AFP) -- General Roosevelt 
Johnson, head of the military high command of the United 
Liberation Movement for Democracy in Liberia, ULIMO, announced 
today in Monrovia that he is "reconciled" with the president of 
the organization, Alhaji Koromah. In a statement broadcast on 
national radio, Gen. Johnson called on all members of the 
movement to unite, and confirmed that all fighters should comply 
with the disarmament process, which started early this week 
throughout the country. [passage omitted] 

