<H3> <TI>   Iranian Minister Briefed on Bakassi Dispute </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AB1203121594 Lagos NTA Television Network in English 2000 
GMT 11 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> AB1203121594 </F>
<F P=104>  Lagos NTA Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The minister of information and culture, Professor 
Jerry Gana, has appealed for the support and understanding of 
friendly nations over the Bakassi Peninsula dispute with 
Cameroon. Receiving the Iranian deputy minister of culture and 
Islamic guidance, 'Ali Larijani, Prof. Gana described Cameroon 
as Nigeria's brother. He said France should allow both 
countries to settle their differences in a true African way. He 
was happy at the evolving relationship between Nigeria and Iran 
and hoped that when the cultural and education agreement between 
the two countries is signed, it will open up other areas of 
cooperation both in economic and technological fields. 

</TEXT>

