<H3> <TI>   Eyadema Discusses Issues With CAR's Agboyibor </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AB1503145694 Lome Radio Lome in French 1230 GMT 15 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> AB1503145694 </F>
<F P=104>  Lome Radio Lome </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> French </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Communique issued by the Action Committee for Renewal in </F>
Lome on 15 March] 
  [Text] The head of state, General Gnassingbe Eyadema, today 
received a delegation of the Action Committee for Renewal [CAR] 
led by CAR Chairman Yaovi Agboyibor, in line with the 
consultations he has initiated following the proclamation of the 
results of the legislative elections by the Supreme Court. 
  The discussions, which lasted from 0855 to 0935, focused 
exclusively on general issues, notably the return of concord, 
social peace, and security in the country to enable the rapid 
resumption of economic activities. The modalities for forming a 
new government were not tackled at the meeting but the CAR 
leader said when the time comes the two opposition parties, who 
won the absolute majority of seats at the National Assembly, 
will hold discussions with the head of state as a united front. 

</TEXT>

